President Obama and Prime Minister Netanyahu had a phone call to discuss the situation in Gaza. The President expressed support for Israel's military operation and condemned attacks by Hamas. He also expressed concern about the increasing number of casualties, including Palestinian civilian deaths. President Obama informed Netanyahu that Secretary of State John Kerry will travel to Cairo to seek an immediate ceasefire based on the 2012 ceasefire agreement. The President emphasized the importance of protecting civilians in Gaza and Israel and stated that the United States will work closely with Israel and regional partners to implement a ceasefire.